Reasoning: The paper deals with complexity notions in learning theory and presents a novel notion of complexity that interpolates between and generalizes some classic existing complexity notions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions information theory (cs.IT) and Bayesian estimators (cs.AI), which further support the likelihood of these sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Rademacher complexity and model complexity, which are relevant to the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Statistics (cs.ST) sub-categories.
